title: Basic Structure of Factory Pattern in C++
notes: Encapsulation of object creation , Easier to manage and extend, Promotes loose coupling

title: Factory Pattern & Factory Registry
detail: To effectively manage a large number of factories—such as 100—in C++, while maintaining scalability and minimizing the impact on existing code, a robust and flexible design approach is essential.
notes: One effective solution is to implement a Factory Registry combined with a reflection-like mechanism. Instead of relying on extensive if-else or switch-case statements for each factory type, this approach utilizes a centralized registry (typically a map or dictionary) to store factory functions, allowing new types to be registered and instantiated dynamically with minimal code changes.
